  <sect1 id="snyaptic-filter">
      <title>Using Filters</title>
      <para>Filters enable you to narrow down the list of shown packages in the main package list.
      </para>

    <sect2 id="synaptic-filter-apply"> 
      <title>To Apply a Predefined Filter</title> 
      <para>&app; comes with a list of predifend filters.</para>

      <table frame="topbot" id="table-synaptic-filters">
	<title>Predefined Filters</title>
        <tgroup cols="2" colsep="0" rowsep="0"><colspec colname="COLSPEC0" colwidth="30*"/>
        <colspec colname="COLSPEC1" colwidth="70*"/>
        <thead>
                <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry valign="top">Filter</entry>
                        <entry valign="top">Description</entry>
                </row>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
                <row>
                        <entry valign="top">All packages</entry>
                        <entry valign="top">Displays all known packages.
                        </entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                        <entry valign="top">Install</entry>
                        <entry valign="top">Displays only currently installed packages.</entry>
	        </row>
                <row>
                        <entry valign="top">Not installed</entry>
                        <entry valign="top">Displays only currently not installed packages.
	                </entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                        <entry valign="top">Upgradable</entry>
                        <entry valign="top">Displays only packages with a later version available.
	                </entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                        <entry valign="top">Broken</entry>
                        <entry valign="top">Displays only packages with broken dependencies.
	                </entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                        <entry valign="top">Programmed Changes</entry>
                        <entry valign="top">Displays only packages queued to be modified.
	                </entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                        <entry valign="top">New in archive</entry>
                        <entry valign="top">Displays only new packages since the last repository
	                update.</entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                        <entry valign="top">Residual</entry>
                        <entry valign="top">Displays only former installed packages that left
	                data or configuration files on the system.</entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                        <entry valign="top">Pkg with Debconf</entry>
                        <entry valign="top">Displays only packages that can be configured through
	                the debian package configuration system, so called debconf.</entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                        <entry valign="top">Oboslete or locally installed</entry>
                        <entry valign="top">Displays only packages that are not (for longer)
		        included in one of the specified repositories.
	                </entry>
                </row>
	</tbody>
       </tgroup>
     </table>


    </sect2>

    <sect2 id="synaptic-filter-edit"> 
      <title>To Edit and Create Filters</title> 

      <para>Filters can be created, deleted and modified in the filter editor. There are two
      ways to start the editor:</para>

      <itemizedlist>
         <listitem>
	    <para>Choose from the menu <menuchoice><guimenu>Search</guimenu><guimenuitem>Edit Filters...</guimenuitem></menuchoice> </para></listitem>
	 <listitem>
	    <para>Click on <guibutton>Filters...</guibutton> in the main window</para>
	 </listitem>
	</itemizedlist>
	 
